On Sunday, October 12, 2003, at 01:50  PM, Wil Haslup wrote:

> What's a petronix?  Is it replaceable?  Is it pricey?

Pertronix Ignitor electronic ignition.  It's not supposed to be 
something you have to replace (though it is pretty easy to do so), and 
costs about $60, IIRC.  It is an aftermarket part that replaces the 
points and condenser.  Several people on this list swear by them.

